The paper discusses a novel information diffusion model on social networks, which involves self-learning mechanisms of individuals. This topic falls under the intersection of several CS sub-categories, including social networks (cs.SOC), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper focuses on the analysis of the model and its theoretical results, which aligns with the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI, followed by cs.SOC, cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.DS.
